this is incorrect behaviour i'm afraid the charset parameter is only defined for documents of type text* that does not apply to applicationx-www-form-urlencoded therefore sending charset would be a specification violation our behaviour is consistent with the w3c html5 specification which says the following if the form element has an accept-charset attribute let the selected character encoding be the result of picking an encoding for the form otherwise if the form element has no accept-charset attribute but the document's character encoding is an ascii-compatible character encoding then that is the selected character encoding otherwise let the selected character encoding be utf-8 we can't do either of the first two things because we don't know what the document or form looks like so we can only do the third if the user wants a different behaviour per the first two points they are required to do it themselves i'm sorry we can't accept this but this is one of those things that seems like it should be simple but is actually quite complex

well fair point i'd reported issues just like this myself the bitter truth is you have to rely on your system package manager and just keep usrlocal empty the best make uninstall is rm -rf usrlocal* the more permanent stuff you keep alive under usrlocal the more pita you'll have with it in the long run however usrlocal shines in playground-style experiments worse you can't trust package authors to do uninstall properly that is another reason why package managers exist so that we have this epic bug occur exactly once and learn from the lesson in that bug an author rolled his own uninstall script and made a fatal typo rm -rf usr libnvidia-currentxorgxorg -- spot the extra space sure we'll fix this in guake but many more other projects won't many projects don't even offer make uninstall -- correctly delegating that function to package managers i'm sorry that you had to have the adventure to figure this out but the advice is just don't make the habit to rely on it

hey @bradymiller apologize for the delay responding drugbank does indeed have a lic model for commercial usage httpswwwdrugbankpluscom has the lic details and contact info i have no idea what the cost would be disclaimer i have nothing to do with them nor am i a lawyer what i do really like is the data which in healthcare it is somewhat spendy as you may well know one downside - i love the uml but nothing close to the extreme one thing i really value is the code generation part @matthewvita is there a webpage on this can't find anything on it seems interesting i could have better stated the concept the more proper term is factory pattern and in my world the concrete implementation is the entity but this isn't canonical in the development world it was proposed by the gof way back in the day in the hallowed tome of 'design patterns' for some light reading i usually follow the abstract factory pattern httpsenwikipediaorgwikiabstract_factory_pattern for something like this the basic idea is to provide the ability to in the abstract support multiple datasets through a single common interface so - drugbank initially since it's free and whatever next from the end user perspective to get the entity ou just say something like drug drug = new drugfactory"drugbank" or whatever arraylist<string> searchresults = drugsearchbyname'haldol' flexible and fun and the factory supplies you the concrete class with drug i can use the same methods as with any other concrete drug class - and expect the same results the key being here is that drug is an interface which forms the contract - it outlines the public methods the concrete class supply as well as the return the concrete class implements the interface and no troubles no bubbles i'll stop here openemr uses mysql and i would bet most users won't be on 57 with the native json support excellent point it would make the ui a little more fun i was thinking we could chuck back json to the ui and then use data binding yet after thinking more about that it opens a can of worms there are a few ways i would recommend putting together a pr and using markdown comments if you need to visualize things maybe try out the foss httppencilevolusvn i'll check out pencil i'm very visual and also lazy i hope it can generate code lastly -- progress i've been getting up to speed on doctrine i like it alot this however introduces a problem with the massive data load this load isn't viable in browser and will need to be cli i couldn't get this functional with the existing framework and rigged up the loader i'm not sure if this creates a technical debt --- i have something approaching a working mvp now regarding initial drug load into a set of tables i'm calling 'kb_drug_domain' --- not that this has to be addressed now but does anyone have any thoughts on isolating the kb tables into a separate database schema or just throw it all together -- i'll post my crummy schema and with luck some use casesdomain concepts for comment later todaytonight

and are similar in scope to the algorithm archive however we are providing something new here that no other project provides so far as i'm aware differences from rosetta code this is fundamentally a book on algorithms focusing on understanding the underlying algorithms the goal here is to provide a reading experience that allows users to fully implement and understand every algorithm from the ground-up in the language of their choice it is definitely not a collection of tasks for the community to complete the implementations provided here are also meant for understanding and we will always try to only merge code that can be understood completely sure we are lacking the power to review certain languages but i have no doubt people will come in to do just that we have the goal of providing sane this text in principle has both a broader scope and expects less background knowledge from the reader obviously we are not there yet on either of those goals but i are doing what i can to get
